---
import scenarios from "../data/scenarios.json";
const scenariosJson = JSON.stringify(scenarios);
const baseUrl = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, "");
---
<section id="demo" class="wide-col py-12">
  <div class="max-w-paper mx-auto mb-8">
    <p class="section-num">4 &middot; Interactive Demo</p>
    <h2>Live Agent Reasoning Trace</h2>
    <p class="mb-4">
      Each scenario below is a recorded execution of the deployed Lambda &mdash; the same JSON tool
      I/O the live system produces, played back at human reading speed. Pick a scenario and press
      <em>Play</em>: you will see the agent reason, call tools, receive structured responses, and
      finally emit a validated routing decision.
    </p>
    <p class="mb-4">
      The third scenario is the most interesting &mdash; it demonstrates ReAct's defining
      property: the agent <em>adapts its plan mid&#8209;loop</em> after discovering CB is
      disabled, skipping unnecessary tool calls and explaining the exclusion in the rationale.
    </p>
    <p class="mb-2">
      <a href={`${baseUrl}/live`} class="pill pill-accent">
        Try the live API &rarr;
      </a>
      <span class="text-sm text-muted ml-2">
        Calls the real deployed Lambda. Pick Bedrock or Anthropic. ~25&ndash;40s per call.
      </span>
    </p>
  </div>

  <div data-trace-root class="max-w-wide mx-auto grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-6">

    <div>
      <div class="bg-white border border-rule rounded-md p-4 mb-4">
        <label class="block text-xs font-sans uppercase tracking-widest text-muted mb-2">
          Scenario
        </label>
        <select
          data-scenario-select
          class="w-full bg-paper border border-rule rounded px-3 py-2 font-serif text-base"
        ></select>
        <p data-scenario-summary class="text-sm text-muted mt-3 leading-relaxed"></p>

        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3 mt-4">
          <button
            data-play-btn
            class="bg-accent text-paper font-sans font-medium px-4 py-2 rounded hover:bg-accent/90 transition disabled:opacity-50 disabled:cursor-not-allowed"
          >
            ▶ Play trace
          </button>
          <button
            data-reset-btn
            class="bg-rule text-ink font-sans font-medium px-4 py-2 rounded hover:bg-rule/80 transition"
          >
            Reset
          </button>

          <label class="flex items-center gap-2 ml-auto text-sm text-muted font-sans cursor-pointer">
            <input data-live-toggle type="checkbox" disabled class="opacity-50 cursor-not-allowed" />
            <span>Use live API <span class="pill pill-warn ml-1">offline</span></span>
          </label>
        </div>

        <div data-live-banner class="hidden mt-3 text-xs text-amber-800 bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded p-2 font-sans">
          Live mode is disabled until AWS Bedrock Anthropic access is granted on the deployment account.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div data-txn-panel></div>

      <div data-decision-panel></div>
    </div>

    <div>
      <div class="term-window sticky top-4">
        <div class="term-header">
          <span class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full bg-red-500/70"></span>
          <span class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full bg-yellow-500/70"></span>
          <span class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full bg-green-500/70"></span>
          <span class="ml-3">routing-agent &middot; us-east-1</span>
        </div>
        <div data-term-body class="term-body"></div>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>

  <script id="trace-scenarios" type="application/json" set:html={scenariosJson} />
  <script>
    import "../scripts/trace-player.ts";
  </script>
</section>
